"Prakash S., Ramesh R., Sheshshayee M.S., Mohan R., Sudhakar M.","Effect of high level iron enrichment on potential nitrogen uptake by marine plankton in the Southern Ocean",2010,"Current Science","99","10",,"1400","1404",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-78650027474&partnerID=40&md5=678ad2256da7b5b2ca83c2f7b47bca1a","Physical Research Laboratory, Navrangpura, Ahmedabad 380 009, India; Department of Crop Physiology, University of Agricultural Sciences, Bangalore 560 065, India; National Centre for Antarctic and Ocean Research, Vasco-da-Gama, Goa 403 804, India; Indian National Centre for Ocean Information Services, Hyderabad 500 055, India","Prakash, S., Physical Research Laboratory, Navrangpura, Ahmedabad 380 009, India, Indian National Centre for Ocean Information Services, Hyderabad 500 055, India; Ramesh, R., Physical Research Laboratory, Navrangpura, Ahmedabad 380 009, India; Sheshshayee, M.S., Department of Crop Physiology, University of Agricultural Sciences, Bangalore 560 065, India; Mohan, R., National Centre for Antarctic and Ocean Research, Vasco-da-Gama, Goa 403 804, India; Sudhakar, M., National Centre for Antarctic and Ocean Research, Vasco-da-Gama, Goa 403 804, India","Iron fertilization of the Southern Ocean is believed to counter the increasing CO2 concentration in the atmosphere and the consequent global warming. Though a number of large scale iron enrichment experiments have been done in the recent past in different parts of the world ocean, little effort has been made to understand the effect of iron enrichment on nitrogen uptake rates and f-ratios. Here we assess the effect of iron addition on N-uptake rates and f-ratio in the Indian sector of the Southern Ocean. This study shows, in contrast to the earlier belief, that iron addition enhances not only nitrate uptake (~ 3×) but it causes a significant increase in ammonium (~ 2×) and urea (~ 3×) uptakes as well. Also, since iron enrichment caused significant increase in the uptake of all N-substrates, its effect on f-ratio was insignificant.","Iron enrichment; Marine plankton; Nitrogen uptake; Southern Ocean",,,,,,,"Chisholm, W.S., Falkowaski, P.G., Cullen, J.J., Dis-crediting ocean fertilization (2001) Science, 294, pp. 309-310; Sarmiento, J.L., Gruber, N., Brzezinski, M.A., Dunne, J.P., High-latitude controls the thermocline nutrients and low latitude biological productivity (2004) Nature, 247, pp. 56-60; Marinov, I., Gnanadesikan, A., Toggweiler, J.R., Sarmiento, J.L., The Southern Ocean biogeochemical divide (2006) Nature, 441. , doi:10.1038/nature04883; Gervais, F., Riebesell, U., Gorbunov, M.Y., Changes in primary productivity and chlorophyll-a in response to iron fertilization in the Southern Ocean frontal zone (2002) Limnol. Oceanogr., 47 (5), pp. 1324-1335; Minas, H.J., Minas, M., Packard, T.T., Productivity in upwelling areas deduced from hydrographic and chemical fields (1986) Limnol. Oceanogr., 31, pp. 1182-1206; Martin, J.H., Gordon, R.M., Fitzwater, S.E., The case of iron (1991) Limnol. Oceanogr., 36 (8), pp. 1793-1802; Martin, J.H., Fitzwater, S.E., Iron deficiency limits phytoplankton growth in the north-east subarctic (1988) Nature, 331, pp. 341-343; Martin, J.H., Gordan, R.M., Fitzwater, S.E., Iron in Antarctic waters (1990) Nature, 345, pp. 156-158; Geider, R.J., Roche, J.La., The role of iron in phytoplankton photosynthesis and the potential of iron limitation of primary productivity in the sea (1994) Photosynth. Res., 39, pp. 275-301; Hutchins, D.A., Iron and the marine phytoplankton community (1995) Prog. Phycol. Res., 11, pp. 1-49; de Baar, H.J.W., Synthesis of iron fertilization experiments: from the iron age in the age of enlightment (2005) J. Geophys. Res., 110. , doi:10.1029/2004JC002601; Singh, A., Prakash, S., Ramesh, R., Sudhakar, M., Ocean fertilization: recent results from the Southern Ocean (2007) Proceedings of the National Conference on Carbon Dioxide Mitigation, , (ed. Sarma, N. S.), Andhra University,